sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Application<br/>(Windows)
    participant TUN as WinTUN<br/>Adapter
    participant Daemon as docker-reach<br/>Daemon
    participant Tunnel as TCP Tunnel<br/>localhost:9999
    participant GW as Gateway<br/>Container
    participant Bridge as Docker<br/>Bridge
    participant C as Target<br/>Container

    Note over App,C: Outbound: Windows → Container

    App->>TUN: IP packet to 172.17.0.3
    Note right of App: Windows route table:<br/>172.17.0.0/16 → 10.0.85.1<br/>via DockerReach adapter

    TUN->>Daemon: Raw IP packet<br/>(kernel → userspace)
    Daemon->>Tunnel: [2B length][IP packet]
    Tunnel->>GW: TCP stream<br/>(Docker port binding)
    Note right of GW: Packet written to tun0<br/>Kernel IP forwarding<br/>src NAT (MASQUERADE)
    GW->>Bridge: Forwarded packet<br/>(via eth0/eth1/ethN)
    Bridge->>C: Delivered to container

    Note over App,C: Return: Container → Windows

    C->>Bridge: Response packet
    Bridge->>GW: Arrives at gateway eth0
    Note right of GW: conntrack de-NATs<br/>Routes via tun0
    GW->>Tunnel: [2B length][IP packet]
    Tunnel->>Daemon: TCP stream
    Daemon->>TUN: Raw IP packet<br/>(userspace → kernel)
    TUN->>App: Delivered to application
